From 4c1cee52455b021d2576b0c1e5ea9f2ba9e106b8 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: petesherratt-collab <petesherratt@googlemail.com>
Date: Wed, 24 Jun 2026 13:24:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Fix local CLI run: codex trust flag, Windows spawn warning,
 troubleshooting

- agents.cli.json: codex exec now passes --skip-git-repo-check so it runs
  outside an approved repo (the trust check was blocking it)
- orchestrate.mjs: on Windows spawn a single command string instead of an
  args array under shell:true, avoiding Node's DEP0190 warning
- README: add a Troubleshooting section (Gemini auth, Codex trust/login)

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_012HJpNBDkteg5t9J97xR7VM
---
 README.md       | 14 ++++++++++++++
 agents.cli.json |  4 ++--
 orchestrate.mjs | 14 +++++++++-----
 3 files changed, 25 insertions(+), 7 deletions(-)

diff --git a/README.md b/README.md
index b0b7197..2f0c8ff 100644
--- a/README.md
+++ b/README.md
@@ -115,6 +115,20 @@ every adversary returns PASS in the same round, the loop stops early. Otherwise
 it runs until `--rounds`. The final draft and a full per-round transcript are
 saved under `runs/`.
 
+## Troubleshooting the local CLIs
+
+A failing adversary doesn't crash the run — it's logged as `ERROR` in that
+round's transcript so the others continue. Common ones:
+
+- **Gemini: `Please set an Auth method` (exit 41)** — not signed in. Run `gemini`
+  once and complete the Google login, or set `GEMINI_API_KEY` in your environment.
+- **Codex: `Not inside a trusted directory and --skip-git-repo-check was not
+  specified`** — `agents.cli.json` already passes `--skip-git-repo-check`; if you
+  changed the command, add that flag back. Also run `codex login` (or set
+  `OPENAI_API_KEY`) first.
+- **Codex: `Reading prompt from stdin...` then nothing** — it *is* reading stdin;
+  any error after that line is auth or the trust check above.
+
